      <h1 class='title'>Water Bill</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c34WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_34ws' title='Col. 34WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c34WS' name='column_34ws' href='#column_34ws' rel='bookmark'>34WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04659'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_159'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-rosindell' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_159' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew Rosindell' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-rosindell" title="Mr Andrew Rosindell">Mr. Rosindell</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04659">To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs what representations she has received from the farming sector about the proposal in the <a href="/bills/water-bill">Water Bill</a> for time-limited licences. [133477]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04660'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_160'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-elliot-morley' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_160' title='Link to this speech by Mr Elliot Morley' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-elliot-morley" title="Mr Elliot Morley">Mr. Morley</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04660">In 1998 the Government first consulted on proposals for all new licences to be issued with a time limit in the consultation paper 'The Review of the Water Abstraction Licensing System in England and Wales'. The majority of responses from the farming sector accepted that there was a need to time limit new abstraction licences. The majority of all the consultation responses received welcomed this proposal, and the Government subsequently included the proposal in the draft <a href="/bills/water-bill">Water Bill</a>.</p><p id="S6CV0412P0-04661">There was similar feedback on our "Water Bill&#x2014;Consultation on draft legislation" which was published in November 2000.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
